      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Lord, in trouble have they visited thee",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Here, at any rate, the redeemed go back in thought to their time of trouble. They remember that what brought them back to God from that alienation which they have confessed (ver. 13) was the affliction which they so long endured. Their present bliss is the result of their former woe, and recalls the thought of it. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "They poured out",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
